title: The New New Thing by Michael Lewis
description:
The New New Thing: A Silicon Valley Story is a book by Michael M. Lewis published in 1999 by W. W. Norton & Company. The book focuses on the founder of several Silicon Valley companies, James H. Clark, and the entrepreneurial culture that dominated the area during the height of the Internet boom.

The book is written with a comedic touch similar to Lewis's earlier book Liar's Poker.

Genre: Economy. Non-fiction
